This allows conforming types to override them in generic contexts. This
comes at the cost of an indirection for each call to them (as the
compiler can’t inline them) but is more flexible for conforming types.

Unshare tvOS scheme

We should release 0.6 with Swift 2.0, but tvOS is only included in Xcode
7.1, which in beta right now. This will cause issues for users trying to
build with Carthage.

To fix this, we should remove the tvOS
scheme from master so that Carthage doesn't see it. We can re-add this
scheme in version 0.7.

Enable free materialize function and use NSError

That bug isn't fixed yet, but this also won't ever compile. Somewhat
Reasonably, you are unable to use a protocol as a concrete type for a
generic type that has a type constraint with that protocol.

To get around this, we should use `NSError` for the error type, since we
can always safely cast from `ErrorType` to `NSError`.

Remove static `materialize` function

Now that we have the initializer that takes a function, this seems less
interesting. Returning a function is much less useful than just passing
a function and getting a Result.

Setting APPLICATION_EXTENSION_API_ONLY to YES

Setting APPLICATION_EXTENSION_API_ONLY to YES

Per the documentation:

```
When enabled, this causes the compiler and linker to
disallow use of APIs that are not available
to app extensions and to disallow linking to frameworks
that have not been built with this setting enabled.
```

Since we're not using any of these APIs, we can safely turn this setting on.

`Result<Bool>.Success(false)`.
